<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">AI-powered editing</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Minute AI includes an AI editing feature that lets you refine the generated minutes
  using natural language instructions.
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Click "AI Edit"</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      This opens a text box where you can give instructions for changes.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Give an instruction</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Type a natural language instruction, for example:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>"Make the executive summary shorter"</li>
      <li>"Add more detail to the action items"</li>
      <li>"Remove the section about budget discussion"</li>
      <li>"Change the tone to be more formal"</li>
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Review the changes</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Amazon Nova Pro will regenerate the affected sections based on your instruction.
      Review the changes and repeat if needed.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Manual editing</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  For direct control over the text, you can edit the minutes manually:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Click "Edit Manually"</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      This enables the rich text editor, allowing you to directly modify the minutes.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Make your changes</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Use the editor to correct names, add context, fix any inaccuracies, or restructure sections.
      The editor supports formatting such as headings, lists, and bold/italic text.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Save your edits</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click "Save" to store your changes. The edited version becomes the current version of the minutes.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Exporting your minutes</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Once you are happy with the minutes, you have several export options:
</p>

<div class="ndx-export-grid">
  <div class="ndx-export-card">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Download</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      Click <strong>"Download"</strong> to get a Word document (.docx) of the minutes, ready to share or archive.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-export-card">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Copy</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      Click <strong>"Copy"</strong> to copy the minutes to your clipboard, ready to paste into an email, document, or collaboration tool.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Exploring templates</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Minute AI comes with several built-in meeting templates, and you can create your own:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Navigate to the Templates page</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click <strong>"Templates"</strong> in the navigation to see all available templates.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Review built-in templates</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Browse the existing templates to see how they are structured. Each template defines
      the sections and format of the generated minutes.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Create a custom template (optional)</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      If you have a specific minute format your organisation uses, you can create a
      custom template that matches it. The AI will then generate minutes following
      your template's structure.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Rate the quality</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Minute AI includes a quality rating feature. After reviewing the generated minutes:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>Use the rating controls to indicate how accurate and useful the minutes are</li>
  <li>This feedback helps improve the system over time</li>
  <li>Consider how the quality compares to manually-written minutes</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">What you have achieved</h3>

